      "content": "The protection of fundamental rights through substantive due process is evident in landmark cases like *Griswold v. Connecticut*, which established a constitutional right to privacy. Furthermore, the right to marry and personal autonomy have been reinforced through this doctrine, as seen in decisions like *Loving v. Virginia*. These rulings demonstrate that the Constitution is not just a set of rules, but a living document actively defending individual freedom against state intrusion.",
      "source": "target",
