    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That's really helpful. One more thing—I want to make sure the students understand why this approach is so much more effective for justice than just sticking to the old-school procedural way of doing things. Could you add a little bit at the end explaining why focusing on the substance of the laws is much more important for protecting human dignity than just making sure the government follows the right \"steps\" or procedures?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Procedural due process only ensures the government plays by the rules, which is insufficient when those rules themselves are unjust. Substantive due process is vital because it demands that the *content* of the law respects basic human dignity and inherent rights. Focusing only on procedure allows oppressive laws to stand if they are enacted correctly, whereas substantive due process actively guards against laws that are fundamentally immoral or tyrannical.",
      "source": "target",
